commentary: Bishoo to Usman Salahuddin, OUT Bishoo strikes in front of his home crowd! Well done solja! Usman doesn't seem too thrilled with the decision. And he has reason to feel disappointed. This is an ordinary ordinary decision. Pitched outside leg! Usman misses the sweep, is hit in front. It's common sense: if a big legbreak is hitting the stumps, it can't have pitched in line. Doesn't apply to Asoka, though

commentary: Sammy to Misbah-ul-Haq, OUT Sammy strikes! Misbah had no clue about this slower offcutter, and Misbah is caught deep in the crease. The inward movement beat the bat, and hit him on the back pad, above the knee roll. The only question here is the height. On replay I notice the knee was bent significantly, creating an impression that he might have been hit high. Dead plumb

commentary: Shahid Afridi to Edwards, no run Drama. Edwards pushed to cover and ran. Sent back. Dived back in as the throw came in. The bat was behind the line, but in air after impact. However, the keeper's attempt at removing the bails missed too. For a second, nobody reacted. Then the keeper realised the bat was still in the same position. Edwards saw him going for it, and tried to press the bat in. It's all tough and go, though, and there is no angle clear enough to conclusively tell either way. Hence not-out
